!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

pause /pɔːz/

(pausing,paused,pauses) 

1. V-I If you pause while you are doing something, you stop for a short period and then continue. 停顿 

例： 'It's rather embarrassing,' he began, and paused. “这很让人尴尬，” 他开始说道，又停顿了片刻。 

例： He talked for two hours without pausing for breath. 他谈了两个小时，没有停下来喘口气。 

2. N-COUNT A pause is a short period when you stop doing something before continuing. 停顿 

例： After a pause Al said sharply: 'I'm sorry if I've upset you.' 停了一下之后艾尔突然说：“如果我让你不安了，我很抱歉。”

